@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Chat.UI

@*
    Help content for the Chat module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Chat is a real-time messaging platform supporting channels, direct messages, file sharing, and audio/video calls. Stay connected with your team in organized conversation spaces.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Channels</h2>
        <p><strong>Public channels</strong> are visible to all users and are great for team-wide discussions. <strong>Private channels</strong> are invite-only for specific groups.</p>
        <p><strong>Creating a channel:</strong> Click the <strong>+</strong> button next to Channels in the sidebar. Choose a name and set visibility (public or private).</p>
        <p><strong>Joining a channel:</strong> Browse available public channels and click <strong>Join</strong>.</p>
        <p><strong>Channel settings:</strong> Channel owners can rename, archive, or delete channels, and manage members.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Direct Messages</h2>
        <p>Start a direct message by clicking a user's name or using the <strong>New DM</strong> option. Direct messages are private between participants.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Messaging</h2>
        <p>Type your message in the input bar at the bottom and press <kbd>Enter</kbd> to send. Use <kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>Enter</kbd> for multi-line messages.</p>
        <p><strong>Formatting:</strong> Support for bold, italic, code blocks, and emoji reactions. Attach files by clicking the attachment icon or dragging and dropping.</p>
        <p><strong>Replying:</strong> Hover over a message and click <strong>Reply</strong> to keep threaded conversations organized.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Audio &amp; Video Calls</h2>
        <p>Start a call from any channel or direct message using the call button in the header. Calls support video, audio-only mode, screen sharing, and participant management.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use channels for topic-specific discussions and DMs for private conversations.</li>
            <li>Pin important messages to keep them easily accessible.</li>
            <li>Use the search bar to find messages across all channels and DMs.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
